This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the linguistic analysis of a large corpus of English text. Additionally, the paper mentions applications such as open information extraction and question answering, which are common topics in the field of natural language processing. 

The paper also involves web-scale crawling and indexing, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

The use of distributional models and word embeddings indicates that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Furthermore, the paper mentions the use of named entity recognition, which is a common task in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper's focus on large-scale data processing and the use of deep learning models suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category cs.DL (Deep Learning).
